text: Michel Heinrich (2015) Michel Heinrich (born February 15, 1946 in Thann, Haut- Rhin) was a member of the National Assembly of France. He represented Vosges' 1st constituency from 2002 to 2017, as a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1946 births Category:Living people Category:People from Thann, Haut-Rhin Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
